summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsSustainable PackagingBenefit's Mighty Fine Brow Pen is the FINEST triple-tip brow pen out there. It instantly fills in brows and mimics the look of natural hair for a full, defined look that lasts and lasts. Shake it up and flick onto clean, dry brows, for your own MIGHTY fine moment.
details: DetailsBenefitsLongwearingRich colorWaterproof, smudge-proof & transfer-proofFinest triple-tip brow penFeaturesFlexible brush tips draw on superfine, 0.1 mm linesSpecial ink feeder for smooth pigment flowItem 2632393How To UseShake, shake, shake!Hold the brush perpendicular to brows to get the finest lines.Flick upwards onto clean, dry brows.Ingredients3.5: Aqua (Water), Butylene Glycol, Dipropylene Glycol, Titanium/Titanium Dioxide, Ammonium Styrene/Acrylates Copolymer, Alcohol, Beheneth-30, Charcoal Powder, Sodium Polyaspartate, Phenoxyethanol, Polyglyceryl-10 Myristate, Pvp, Pentylene Glycol, Sodium Dehydroacetate, Sodium Metaphosphate, Ammonium Acrylates Copolymer, Citric Acid, Aluminum Hydroxide, Disodium Edta, Silica, Xanthan Gum, Simethicone. May Contain (+/-): Ci 77491, Ci 77492, Ci 77499 (Iron Oxides), Ci 77891 (Titanium Dioxide).Disclaimer: Product ingredient listings are updated periodically. reviews.headline: Mades up for brow loss due to cancer treatment
reviews.comments: My brows are mostly gone due to cancer treatments. It was great to find a product that works to create the look of eyebrows! I use it with the eyebrow wax and by itself. Love it beast to apply.

reviews.headline: Easy to use
reviews.comments: This product is easy to use.  It looks great and matches mu brows perfectly.

reviews.headline: It's become my go to
reviews.comments:
I love the 3 points on this brow pen easy to make balanced even strokes. Although I have my brows microbladed as I have very sparse brows from radiation therapy this brow pen finishes my brows to look just as I like. If I want a more dramatic going out look I can do it with just a few strokes 
This is my daily go to.

reviews.headline: My eyebrows are back!
reviews.comments: I thought I would never have eyebrows again, and then the magic happened. So easy to use! I will never be without eyebrows again!

reviews.headline: High hopes yet disappointing
reviews.comments: I had high hopes for this pen but it's pretty much junk. Barely pigmented and for those of use with little to no eyebrows it doesnt color/fill in on skin so it just leaves uneven, patchy brows

reviews.comments: Does not smear or rub off

reviews.headline: This fine brow pen is great!
reviews.comments: I love this brow pen.  As I've aged, my eyebrows have gotten lighter.  This brown pen gives me definition and is very much like my original color.  I will buy this product again!

reviews.headline: Outstanding
reviews.comments: The first one I ordered was emptyâ€¦. I wasn't sure I was even using it right. I took it back to the store and exchanged it for a full and a bit darker too. Now it's perfect. It's the greatest brush. Very natural looking strokes for eyebrows.

reviews.headline: Poor packaging, good product
reviews.comments: I have used this brow pen about 10 times and liked it. Unfortunately the ink cartridge detatched from the packaging and it stuck to the lid. While trying to detach the piece, the ink cartridge opened and started leaking on my hands. It is a shame because I did like this product.

reviews.headline: I found "THE ONE"
reviews.comments: Ok, I was blessed with sparse eyebrows ðŸ˜ðŸ˜£! Im 42 and have been shading /drawing in my brows since I was 13 . About 13 years ago I discovered Anastasia brow wiz, and yes she has been good to me, but I've never been 100% satisfied. So, I thought I would try the hair stroke method.. And I love it! I'm sure its only going to get better because today is my first day, but so far I am so happy with this product and it will be one of my forever items!

reviews.headline: Works great!
reviews.comments: It works well, pigment is great. Easy to use. Only deducted one star because it has a reddish undertone

reviews.headline: Not Worth The Money
reviews.comments: I'm a longtime brow guru, my closest circle depends on my honest brow product reviews on what to get.  I recommend going with a long lasting cheaper version of these type of pens. Your budget will thank me.

reviews.headline: Does not Dispense enough product!
reviews.comments: The idea of having 3 small brushes is great. Worked great the first couple of days but started to not go on properly and eventually the brush wouldn't dispense more product. I have tried everything. Eventually just put it in the trash.

reviews.headline: BRING BACK THE OLD MICROFILLING PEN PLEASE
reviews.comments: Idk why the decided to remake this pen. The neutral medium brown shade is SO WARM and too pigmented compared to the old medium brown. The applicatior is so hard to us as well and my brows ended up looking so patchy and uneven. I woukd return this but i sadly threw away the box. Please bring back the old pen and old formula it was literally perfect ðŸ˜­ðŸ˜­ðŸ˜­

reviews.headline: Says it's waterproof
reviews.comments: I have no brows due to overplucking in the 70's (who knew) and chemo treatments in the early 2000. I MISS the Brow Microfilling Pen. It had better application and lasted for 2 days. After applying the Mighty Fine Brow pen imagine my shock when on a hot day I returned home to find I was missing half a brow on my right side. It's like it melted away.

reviews.headline: How do you dispense the color?
reviews.comments: I like the brush but I'm not seeing how you can dispense any color. It does not twist and I don't recall any instructions. Please advise!

faceoff_positive.comments: Here's a positive review: Title: A Game-Changer for Brows - Benefit's Mighty Fine Brow Pen! Rating: 5/5 stars I'm absolutely obsessed with Benefit's new Mighty Fine Brow Pen! As someone who's struggled to find the perfect brow product, I can confidently say this pen has exceeded my expectations. The innovative three-point tip allows for incredibly realistic, hair-like strokes that mimic the natural shape and texture of my brows. The formula is richly pigmented, yet subtle and buildable, making it perfect for creating a natural, everyday look or a more dramatic, glam look. What truly impresses me, however, is the longevity of this product. It genuinely lasts all day without smudging, fading, or requiring touch-ups. Whether I'm running errands, working out, or just living my best life, my brows stay perfectly in place. If you're in the market for a reliable, easy-to-use brow product that delivers stunning results, look no further than Benefit's Mighty Fine Brow Pen. Trust me, your brows will thank you! Gifted by benefit cosmetics Pros: Innovative three-point tip for realistic brow hairs Richly pigmented, yet subtle and buildable formula Long-lasting, smudge-proof wear Easy to use, even for brow beginners! Cons: None!
faceoff_positive.headline: STUNNING

faceoff_negative.comments: I have cancer and as a maleâ€¦ I'm not exactly happy, but I can deal with the fact that I'm balding. I can't however get comfortable with not having eyebrows. The Goof Proof 2.5 is a really great help. I figured that this "pen" would be akin to GP. Do you have to wet this, or add the color from another product? I was happy that I got the med. N brown too (that's another topic for another time, but you ALL know that not everyone is a "warm" toned, but there's a lot of choices for them here). The products I've used from Benefit are exceptional, but even the med. brown is just another "warm" shade. I have dark ashy blonde hair. The Goof Proof 2.5 is a nice grayed blonde, this pen is translucent "warm" beige. Still a fan of the products I've been using, this one needs some tweaking as do the shades that don't include ash toned hair colors
